17:
What's going on here?
I was in the forest one moment, and 
now I'm... wherever this is.
22: Oof... There's no end to them!
34:
Where'd all these guys even come 
from?
37:
I'll distract them. Alk, take the 
opportunity and—
48:
We'll handle the ones in front—don't 
let them near her, Alk!
51:
Just let me handle it!
Elvish... Bow!
61:
Much obliged, stranger. My name is 
Light. And this here is—
64:
Alk's the name! Thanks for saving our 
bacon.
68:
I just did what anyone else would've. 
I'm Arisa, by the way.
I was training in the forest, and 
somehow ended up here... Do you 
know how I can get back?
76:
I guess that's a no.
Actually... Do you know where I am?
78:
I was searching for the Morning Star 
in hopes that I'd find my friend, but 
somehow I've ended up... here.
86:
Wait, you've never heard of the 
Morning Star?
90:
I see. You must be from another world,
then.
94: A-another world? What do you mean?
97:
It may be hard to take in, but you 
must've traversed into this world 
somehow.
100:
I'm not sure if it'll help or not, but this 
place isn't our original world either.
105:
No way... What am I supposed to do 
now?
117:
Arisa, there's something we'd like to 
show you.
121:
Welcome to Starview Village. I am its 
keeper, Stella.
127:
Gosh, this really IS a different world, 
isn't it? How am I ever gonna get 
back?
134:
I'm looking for a friend. Her name's 
Losaria.
135:
Is there a way I could find my way 
back to my original world?
140:
Sorry if this seems sudden, but I... 
I have to find her.
143: I see. Let's find her together.
146:
By using the World Flipper, we'll be 
able to traverse many worlds.
149:
Yours may be among them. We'll 
help you find it.
152:
You're telling me this... door can take 
me back home somehow?
156:
There are many worlds. It may take 
some time.
157:
However, I am sure we can find it if 
we search together.
160:
(A "World Flipper"? I've never seen 
anything like this before. But today's 
been a day full of firsts, I guess.)
162:
(I can't afford to be afraid now. And 
this may be my best bet at finding 
Losaria for now.)
164:
O-okay! I'd be glad to join you guys 
on your journey.
169: Great! We're happy to have you.
173:
Your bow skills were remarkable. We'll 
be counting on your talents, Arisa.
175:
Oh, no! I-I'm still getting the hang of 
things. Losaria, on the other hand, 
now SHE knows how to handle a bow. 
*sigh*
183:
Yeah. She's everything to me. So, 
please... I hope that we can help each 
other out for the time being.
187:
Of course! And no need to be so 
formal—we're all on the same team 
now.
190:
Yeah, you're right! Thanks for having 
me on the team.
194: Just wait, Losaria. I'm on my way!
